Manchester City have a narrow lead at the halfway stage of their Champions League semi-final tie against Real Madrid after a thrilling 4-3 win at the Etihad. In an astonishing European match that could have finished any score, City took a two-goal lead inside 11 minutes as Gabriel Jesus and Kevin De Bruyne got them off to a flying start. Karim Benzema got his 40th goal of the season though, completely against the run of play, to halve the deficit. Phil Foden extended the lead shortly after the break, only for Vinicius Junior to respond almost immediately with a brilliant solo effort. Bernardo Silva lashed home from the edge of the box to make it 4-2, but there was still time for Benzema to step up to the spot and dispatch an impudent panenka